Kind: captions
Language: en-US

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.000
Hi, welcome to the mvp race: MLB player statistics in the 2022 season. 

00:00:07.315 --> 00:00:13.101
The very first thing you can see is the introduction and background information of our website.

00:00:14.045 --> 00:00:16.822
You can scroll down to enter the visualization part.

00:00:19.547 --> 00:00:25.193
Which is consisting with four sub-parts, on the top left, we have player profile.

00:00:25.193 --> 00:00:27.916
on the top right, we have the diamond progress bar.

00:00:28.573 --> 00:00:31.655
In the middle, we have a dugout for selected attribute.

00:00:31.923 --> 00:00:36.299
At the bottom, we have bar graph that compare player to MLB average.

00:00:38.125 --> 00:00:43.559
To show the visualization, we start with the two dropdown which is above the player profile. 

00:00:44.651 --> 00:00:48.832
You are able to select a player name and a statistical category. 

00:00:49.235 --> 00:00:51.397
Let’s say we select CJ Abrams.

00:00:55.307 --> 00:00:59.868
 You are now able to see his headshot and statistics in his profile.

00:01:00.690 --> 00:01:03.257
Also, you can see the bar graph also shows up.

00:01:05.155 --> 00:01:07.089
You can hover the bar to see the value.  

00:01:08.375 --> 00:01:13.888
Don’t forget to select a attribute in the statistical category dropdown to activate the diamond and dugout. 

00:01:15.584 --> 00:01:17.280
Let’s say we choose triples.

00:01:20.939 --> 00:01:22.872
You can now see the diamond progress bar change.

00:01:23.534 --> 00:01:29.756
The value inside the circle indicates how close his triple compares to all time highest triple in MLB. 

00:01:30.898 --> 00:01:35.279
In the dugout you can also see the five highest triple in MLB.

00:01:36.151 --> 00:01:38.743
It is okay to change the player or attribute.

00:01:39.624 --> 00:01:40.505
 Enjoy !

